<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="150" pageId="2" pageNumber="149" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1840,2034]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,827]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="150" pageId="2" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1944,1967]" pageId="2" pageNumber="149">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Male (Female unknown). Dorsal shield with U-shaped area of smaller pores only slightly raised laterally, not reaching caudal margin of dorsal shield, more close to each other in the middle part; gnathosomal bay V-shaped; a short ridge extending anterolaterally from suture line between Cx-III and Cx-IV; Cxgl– 
<number box="[1085,1098,2011,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="149" value="2.0">2</number>
anterior to gonopore, the gland portion absent; three pairs of acetabula; swimming setae absent; I–L- 
<number box="[896,908,152,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" value="6.0">6</number>
slender (L/H ratio 3.0); P- 
<number box="[1198,1211,152,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" value="4.0">4</number>
stout (L/H ratio 
<number box="[1393,1427,152,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="150" value="2.1">2.1</number>
) with an enlarged, forward-directed tubercle bearing two small setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
